<task id="040" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>Migrate ContextPaneController to shared PaneHeader + stage label rename (FR-17, FR-22)</title>
    <phase>Phase D — Context pane</phase>
    <status>completed</status>
    <estimated-hours>3</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>010</dependencies>
    <blocks>042</blocks>
    <tags>react, frontend, fluent-ui, refactoring</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Modifies a load-bearing .tsx file (ContextPaneController) whose existing header is the canonical visual reference for the entire PaneHeader primitive. ADR-012 (load-bearing) compliance is at stake: this is the consumption site that proves PaneHeader visual parity. Stage-label rename is small but ships with the same file edit.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>D</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Touches ContextPaneController.tsx — the same file edited by task 042 (welcome-stage widget swap). Must serialize.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Migrate `ContextPaneController.tsx` to consume the shared `<PaneHeader>` primitive from
    `@spaarke/ui-components` (Phase A task 010) per FR-17, replacing the existing inline
    header JSX. The existing header style at lines 142-171 and 691-700 is THE canonical
    visual reference for PaneHeader — preserve every aspect of that style (icon color,
    typography, spacing, right-slot composition). Additionally, rename the welcome-stage
    label from "Gallery" to "Get Started" per FR-22 by updating `stageLabelMap.welcome`.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    React 19 + Fluent v9 frontend developer experienced refactoring three-pane shell
    surfaces, comfortable replacing inline JSX with a shared primitive while preserving
    pixel-perfect visual parity. Familiar with PaneEventBus subscriber graphs and stage
    lifecycle wiring.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `ContextPaneController.tsx` renders `<PaneHeader title="Context" icon={DocumentRegular}&gt;`
    from `@spaarke/ui-components` at the top of the pane. The right-slot of PaneHeader
    contains the existing stage label (e.g., "Get Started" on welcome stage). The
    `stageLabelMap.welcome` value is changed from "Gallery" to "Get Started". Visual
    rendering before and after this change is INDISTINGUISHABLE in both light and dark
    modes (the existing style IS the canonical reference). All tab-related local state
    is preserved (this task does NOT touch widget-resolution logic — that is task 042).
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      FR-17 migrates the Context pane to the unified PaneHeader primitive established in
      Phase A (task 010). Critically, the existing header style in ContextPaneController
      (lines 142-171, 691-700) is the design source-of-truth for PaneHeader itself — so
      after migration the Context pane should look pixel-identical. This task pairs the
      header migration with FR-22 (stage label rename) since both edit the same file and
      both are foundational for the Phase D welcome-state redesign. The actual welcome-stage
      widget swap (GetStartedCardsWidget vs PlaybookGalleryWidget) is task 042.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/context/ContextPaneController.tsx</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">PaneHeader is consumed from `@spaarke/ui-components` — do NOT duplicate the component locally. Import via the package path, not a relative file path. The existing inline header JSX MUST be replaced, not retained.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Icon color must use `tokens.colorBrandForeground1`. No hex literals, no `rgba(...)` literals, no Fluent v8. Header background and dividers must consume Fluent v9 neutral-background/stroke tokens.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">React 19 only. No React 16 fallbacks. Do not add `useEffect` dependency-array workarounds for removed inline header state.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-025">DocumentRegular icon comes from `@fluentui/react-icons` (Fluent v9). No new SVG web resources.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">No `accessToken` props or state introduced. Any BFF calls in the pane continue to use `authenticatedFetch`. Do not snapshot tokens.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">PaneHeader visual style MUST match the pre-change ContextPaneController header exactly — this file's existing style IS the canonical reference (per plan §2 Discovered Resources). Pixel-identical parallel rendering is the acceptance bar.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">This task touches ONLY `ContextPaneController.tsx` and only the header JSX + `stageLabelMap.welcome`. Widget-resolution logic for welcome stage is OWNED by task 042 — do NOT modify it here. Leave a clear TODO comment if the rightSlot composition needs adjustment in 042.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-design-system.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-028-spaarke-auth-architecture.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/plan.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/auth/spaarke-sso-binding.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/webresource/full-page-custom-page.md</file>
      <file>docs/guides/SHARED-UI-COMPONENTS-GUIDE.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Read ContextPaneController.tsx — note canonical header">
      Open `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/context/ContextPaneController.tsx`. Read
      lines 142-171 and 691-700 carefully — this inline header JSX is the canonical visual
      model. Note the icon usage, typography classes, spacing tokens, divider, and right-slot
      composition (the stage label currently lives in this slot).
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Add PaneHeader + DocumentRegular imports">
      Import `PaneHeader` from `@spaarke/ui-components` (export added by task 010) and
      `DocumentRegular` from `@fluentui/react-icons`. Use the package path, not a relative
      import.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Replace inline header JSX with PaneHeader">
      Replace the inline header JSX (the block currently rendering icon + "Context" title +
      stage label) with `&lt;PaneHeader title="Context" icon={&lt;DocumentRegular /&gt;} rightSlot={&lt;StageLabel ... /&gt;} /&gt;`.
      The existing stage label JSX (or a small inline span using `stageLabelMap[stage]`) moves
      into the `rightSlot` prop verbatim. Remove any now-orphaned local styles that the
      shared PaneHeader supplies.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Rename stageLabelMap.welcome — Gallery → Get Started">
      Locate `stageLabelMap` (or equivalent constant). Change `welcome: 'Gallery'` to
      `welcome: 'Get Started'`. Leave other stage labels untouched.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Visual parity check — light + dark mode">
      Build SpaarkeAi (`npm run build` against the solution). In Vite dev or Power Apps host,
      compare the new Context pane header against the pre-change version (git stash + reload
      if needed). Spacing, typography, icon alignment, and right-slot positioning MUST be
      indistinguishable. Repeat in dark mode. Capture screenshots if available; commit a
      short visual-diff note in `notes/visual-diffs/040-pane-header.md` if any subtle
      discrepancies surface.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Verify welcome-stage label reads Get Started">
      Load the SpaarkeAi welcome state. Confirm the right-side stage label in the Context
      pane header reads "Get Started" (not "Gallery"). Switch to a non-welcome stage and
      confirm the corresponding label still renders correctly.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">Read ContextPaneController.tsx + the new PaneHeader source for prop signature</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">Replace inline header JSX, add imports, rename stage label constant</tool>
    <tool name="Grep">Find any other consumers of `stageLabelMap.welcome` that may need updating</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">Run `npm run build` against SpaarkeAi to verify no TS / lint errors</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/context/ContextPaneController.tsx</output>
    <output type="report">Task completion report confirming PaneHeader migration with visual parity + stage label rename</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`ContextPaneController.tsx` imports `PaneHeader` from `@spaarke/ui-components` and `DocumentRegular` from `@fluentui/react-icons`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">The inline header JSX block (previously lines ~142-171) is replaced with a single `&lt;PaneHeader title="Context" icon={&lt;DocumentRegular /&gt;} rightSlot={...} /&gt;` element.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">The stage label (e.g., "Get Started" on welcome) renders inside the PaneHeader rightSlot.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`stageLabelMap.welcome === 'Get Started'` (renamed from "Gallery").</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Visual parity check confirms the new header is indistinguishable from the pre-change header in both light and dark modes (the existing style IS the canonical reference).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`npm run build` succeeds with no new TS / lint errors.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No `accessToken` props introduced (ADR-028 invariants preserved).</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <ui-tests>
    <test name="PaneHeader visual parity — light mode">
      Open SpaarkeAi welcome state. Verify Context pane shows `<PaneHeader>` with DocumentRegular
      icon in brand color, title "Context", and right-slot showing "Get Started". Compare side-by-side
      against the pre-change reference — they must be indistinguishable.
    </test>
    <test name="Dark Mode Compliance (ADR-021, NFR-06)">
      Toggle dark mode in D365 settings (or Vite dev theme toggle). Verify:
      <steps>
        <step>Header background adapts via Fluent v9 neutral-background tokens (no white in dark mode)</step>
        <step>Title text adapts via neutral-foreground tokens (no black in dark mode)</step>
        <step>DocumentRegular icon stays in brand foreground 1 (visible in both themes)</step>
        <step>Divider/stroke uses Fluent v9 stroke tokens</step>
      </steps>
    </test>
    <test name="Stage label reads Get Started on welcome">
      Load welcome state. Confirm right-side stage label in Context pane header reads "Get Started" (not "Gallery").
    </test>
    <test name="Stage label switches correctly on non-welcome stages">
      Trigger a stage transition (e.g., via a chat message that moves the shell into active stage). Confirm the stage label updates to the appropriate non-welcome value.
    </test>
    <test name="No console errors">
      Open browser devtools. Confirm zero JavaScript errors or React warnings on pane mount and stage transition.
    </test>
  </ui-tests>

